15/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- According to an announcement Wednesday (March 14th), Deputy Foreign Minister Gergana Grancharova is expected to be appointed as the new Minister of European Affairs, filling the post left vacant since Meglena Kuneva became EU Commissioner for Consumer Protection a few months ago. On Tuesday, Grancharova said that joining the Schengen common border control and visa space is the top priority. (Dnevnik - 15/03/07; Darik, Bulgarian government website - 14/03/07)
